example: For a(7)=1, the heptomino with exactly fourfold symmetry and axes of symmetry parallel to the diagonals of the cells is composed of two 2 X 2 squares with one cell in common. For a(8)=1, the octomino is composed of a 2 X 2 square and the four cells adjacent to two nonadjacent cells of that square.
